---
import MainLayout from "../../layouts/MainLayout.astro";

const snapshot = [
  { label: "Industry", value: "Marketplace / Fintech" },
  { label: "Role", value: "Global Head of Product Design" },
  { label: "Scope", value: "8 designers, 3 researchers, global cross-functional teams" },
  { label: "Key Outcomes", value: "2M+ SMBs, $1.2B GMV, new fintech revenue streams" },
];

const decisions = [
  {
    title: "Discovery-led marketplace design",
    text: "We shifted from transaction-first flows to discovery-driven experiences, helping SMBs find products, compare options, and make better purchasing decisions.",
  },
  {
    title: "Fintech as infrastructure, not feature",
    text: "Payments, credit, and financial tools were embedded directly into workflows, enabling SMBs to operate more efficiently without switching systems.",
  },
  {
    title: "Mobile-first for low-literacy environments",
    text: "We designed for real-world usage conditions—ensuring accessibility, clarity, and usability for users with varying levels of digital familiarity.",
  },
  {
    title: "Unified vendor and operations model",
    text: "We created a single system that connected procurement, fulfillment, and financial visibility for both SMBs and suppliers.",
  },
];

const outcomes = [
  "Enabled a unified marketplace and fintech ecosystem serving 2M+ SMBs across Latin America.",
  "Generated $1.2B+ in annual gross merchandise value through integrated platform capabilities.",
  "Unlocked new revenue streams through embedded financial services (credit, payments).",
  "Improved operational efficiency for SMBs by reducing fragmentation across tools and workflows.",
  "Positioned AB InBev as a digital transformation leader in the SMB marketplace ecosystem.",
];
---

<MainLayout title="SMB Marketplace & Fintech Ecosystem | Jorge Obando">
  <section class="case-study-page">

    <!-- HERO -->
    <section class="hero">
      <p class="eyebrow">AB InBev / Z-Tech</p>
      <h1>SMB Marketplace & Fintech Ecosystem</h1>
      <p class="lead">
        Transforming fragmented SMB operations into a unified marketplace and fintech
        platform—unlocking new revenue streams, improving efficiency, and enabling
        millions of businesses to scale.
      </p>
    </section>

    <!-- SNAPSHOT -->
    <section class="snapshot-grid">
      {snapshot.map((item) => (
        <article class="snapshot-card">
          <p class="snapshot-label">{item.label}</p>
          <p class="snapshot-value">{item.value}</p>
        </article>
      ))}
    </section>

    <!-- SITUATION -->
    <section class="content-section">
      <h2>The situation</h2>
      <p>
        Small and medium-sized businesses (SMBs) across Latin America operated in highly
        fragmented environments. Procurement, payments, inventory, and vendor management
        were handled through disconnected tools—often informal channels such as messaging
        apps, phone calls, and manual processes.
      </p>
      <p>
        This fragmentation limited growth, reduced efficiency, and prevented SMBs from
        accessing financial services that could expand their operations.
      </p>
    </section>

    <!-- CHALLENGE -->
    <section class="content-section">
      <h2>The challenge</h2>
      <p>
        The challenge was to design a platform that could unify procurement, payments,
        and financial services into a single system—while remaining usable for a highly
        diverse user base with varying levels of digital literacy.
      </p>
      <p>
        This required balancing marketplace dynamics, fintech capabilities, regional
        complexity, and real-world operational constraints across multiple countries.
      </p>
    </section>

    <!-- ROLE -->
    <section class="content-section">
      <h2>My role</h2>
      <p>
        As Global Head of Product Design, I led design strategy across a distributed,
        cross-functional organization. I worked closely with product, engineering, and
        business stakeholders to align platform direction and ensure the experience
        supported both user needs and business objectives.
      </p>
      <p>
        My focus was on shaping a system that could scale across markets while maintaining
        clarity, usability, and operational consistency.
      </p>
    </section>

    <!-- HOW I OPERATED -->
    <section class="content-section">
      <h2>How I operated</h2>
      <div class="cards-grid two-up">

        <article class="info-card">
          <h3>Reframed the problem</h3>
          <p>
            We moved from improving isolated tools to designing a connected ecosystem
            that integrated marketplace and financial services into a single platform.
          </p>
        </article>

        <article class="info-card">
          <h3>Structured the platform</h3>
          <p>
            We defined core workflows and system architecture that could support
            procurement, payments, and operations across multiple markets.
          </p>
        </article>

        <article class="info-card">
          <h3>Aligned global teams</h3>
          <p>
            I worked across regions and functions to align priorities, ensure consistency,
            and build a shared understanding of platform direction.
          </p>
        </article>

        <article class="info-card">
          <h3>Enabled scalable execution</h3>
          <p>
            We established reusable patterns and systems that allowed faster rollout
            across countries without redesigning from scratch.
          </p>
        </article>

      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- DECISIONS -->
    <section class="content-section">
      <h2>Key decisions</h2>
      <div class="cards-grid one-up">
        {decisions.map((item) => (
          <article class="info-card">
            <h3>{item.title}</h3>
            <p>{item.text}</p>
          </article>
        ))}
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- OUTCOMES -->
    <section class="content-section">
      <h2>Outcomes</h2>
      <div class="outcomes-card">
        <ul>
          {outcomes.map((item) => (
            <li>{item}</li>
          ))}
        </ul>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- REFLECTION -->
    <section class="content-section">
      <h2>Reflection</h2>
      <p>
        This work demonstrates how design can operate at the level of business systems—
        not just interfaces—connecting marketplace dynamics, financial services, and
        operational workflows into a cohesive platform that creates real economic impact.
      </p>
    </section>

    <!-- NEXT -->
    <section class="content-section next-step">
      <h2>Next case study</h2>
      <p>
        Continue to <a href="/case-studies/global-servicing-platform">Global Servicing Platform</a>.
      </p>
    </section>

  </section>
</MainLayout>

<style>
  .case-study-page {
    padding: 2.5rem 0 5rem;
  }

  .hero {
    max-width: 800px;
    margin-bottom: 3rem;
  }

  .eyebrow {
    margin: 0 0 0.6rem;
    font-size: 0.72rem;
    font-weight: 600;
    letter-spacing: 0.08em;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    color: #a33a3a;
  }

  .hero h1 {
    margin: 0;
    font-size: clamp(2.5rem, 4vw, 4.15rem);
    line-height: 1.05;
    letter-spacing: -0.03em;
  }

  .lead {
    margin-top: 1.2rem;
    font-size: 1.1rem;
    line-height: 1.85;
    color: #555;
    max-width: 760px;
  }

  .snapshot-grid {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: repeat(4, 1fr);
    gap: 1rem;
    margin-bottom: 3rem;
  }

  .snapshot-card,
  .info-card,
  .outcomes-card {
    border: 1px solid var(--divider);
    border-radius: 16px;
    background: #fff;
  }

  .snapshot-card {
    padding: 1.2rem;
  }

  .snapshot-label {
    font-size: 0.75rem;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    color: #777;
  }

  .snapshot-value {
    margin-top: 0.4rem;
  }

  .content-section {
    margin-top: 3rem;
    padding-top: 2.5rem;
    border-top: 1px solid var(--divider);
  }

  .cards-grid {
    display: grid;
    gap: 1rem;
  }

  .cards-grid.two-up {
    grid-template-columns: repeat(2, 1fr);
  }

  .info-card {
    padding: 1.4rem;
  }

  .outcomes-card {
    padding: 1.4rem;
  }

  @media (max-width: 768px) {
    .snapshot-grid,
    .cards-grid.two-up {
      grid-template-columns: 1fr;
    }
  }
</style>